  "text": "6) The microstructures display various taphonomic features, such as deformation and breakage. Wall textures vary from granular to hyaline, even within a single specimen [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . 7) Many of the lenses are composed of a central spheroid body and surrounding sheet-like appendage called flange, which displays some variations of surface textures such as striation and reticulation [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Central bodies of most lenses, if not all, display intricate, internal network of organic materials (alveolar structure) [CITATION_5] .",
